Chunghwa Telecom Co., Ltd. (NYSE:CHT) Experiences Lighter than Average Trading Volume - Highlight Press

























































Highlight PressBreaking Tech News, Entertainment, Mortgages and More
Chunghwa Telecom Co., Ltd. (NYSE:CHT) Experiences Lighter than Average Trading Volume
July 12, 2017 By Clarence Martin Tweet        Advertisement





Chunghwa Telecom Co., Ltd. shares had a trading volume of 159K by the end of trading on Wednesday.  Volume was down 21.84% under the stocks average daily volume. 
 Here are a few additional firms who have increased or decreased their stake in (CHT).   Bank Of Montreal /can/ augmented its stake by buying 29,700 shares an increase of 33.8%. Bank Of Montreal /can/ controls 117,700 shares worth $4,145,000. The value of the position overall is up by 38.6%. Hexavest Inc. grew its investment by buying 205,666 shares an increase of 457.3% from 03/31/2017 to 06/30/2017. Hexavest Inc. now controls 250,640 shares valued at $8,828,000. The total value of its holdings increased 477.7%.
 Capstone Asset Management Co reduced its position by shedding 3,550 shares a decrease of 4.1% in the quarter. Capstone Asset Management Co currently owns 83,924 shares with a value of $2,956,000. The total value of its holdings decreased 0.5%. As of the end of the quarter Symphony Asset Management LLC had sold  a total of 931 shares trimming its stake by 13.7%. The value of the investment in (CHT) went from $230,000 to $213,000 decreasing 7.4% quarter over quarter.
  On May 3, 2016 the stock rating was rated “Buy” according to a UBS report which was a boost from the previous “” rating. On April 28 the stock rating was downgraded to “Neutral” from “” in an announcement from Citigroup.





 On April 22 the company was upgraded from “” to “Hold” by analysts at HSBC. Credit Suisse initiated coverage with a rating of “Neutral”.
 The company is trading up by 0.62% since yesterday’s close of $35.38.  The company also recently announced a dividend for shareholders to be paid on Friday the 1st of September 2017.  The dividend will be $0.408 per share for the quarter or $1.63 on an annualized basis.  This dividend amount will represent a yeild of $4.62.  The ex-dividend date will be on Tuesday the 19th of July 2016. 
 Shares of the company are trading at $35.60 which is just over $35.52, the 50 day moving average and barely above the 200 day moving average of $33.64.  The 50 day moving average moved up $0.08 and the 200 day average went up $1.96 or +5.83%. 
 Chunghwa Telecom Co., Ltd.’s P/E ratio is 21.84 and market capitalization is 27.62B. 
 Chunghwa Telecom Co., Ltd., launched on June 15, 1996, is a telecommunications service provider in Taiwan. The Business’s segments include Domestic fixed communications business, Mobile communications business, Internet business, International fixed communications business and Others. The Company also focuses on selected information and communication technology (ICT) services and advanced developments. In addition to developing ICT businesses, it also pursues ICT projects from both public and private sectors..






